<div id="Idea_2706"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2706-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2706">Fraud waist and abuse, Dep of Energy...&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">skidadsr</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Carter established the Dep. of Energy to figure out how the US could become less reliant on foreign oil and now 20+ years later the US is still very reliant on foreign oil, probably even more so.  So why do they exist if they/it cannot get the job done after over 20 years?  Is it only strange to me that billions of tax dollars are going into this Dep. and nothing to show for it? </div>
